Description: Bust of Commodus right, laureate, wearing paludamentum and cuirass. (obverse)
Dionysus standing left; in right hand, kantharos; over left shoulder, thyrsos; at feet, panther. (reverse)
State: Associated with: Roman Empire Ancient Greece and Rome: Roman Empire
Curator's comments: Previously attributed by Head (1886) to Marcus Aurelius.
